Ekiti State Governor, Dr. Kayode Fayemi, has promised to continually work out plans to make senior citizens in the state live a good life after retirement. He also stated that the need for a virile civil service has brought about reforms put in place by his administration. The governor said this was being done through timely payment for their gratuities and pensions as well as activation of other social investments plans for them. Fayemi made the declaration d in Ado-Ekiti during a special send forth reception in honour of two retired heads of service and 42 permanent secretaries, who had retired from the state’s public service between 2012 and 2019. The governor in a statement by the his Chief Press Secretary, Mr. Yinka Oyebode, unveiled plans by his administration to build a recreational and wellness centre with modern facilities for senior citizens in Ado-Ekiti, the state capital. The governor said the idea of building an elderly people’s resort and wellness centre for the senior citizens was borne out of respect for the elderly as well as the wise counsel of the Ekiti Council of Elders. “Let me use this opportunity to restate the determination of the present Administration to make the welfare of all the Senior Citizens in the State a priority, through prompt payment of their gratuities and pensions. “Equally, based on our respect for elders and the wise counsel of the Ekiti Council of Elders, we are building a recreational Elderly People’s Resort and Wellness Centre in Ado Ekiti”, he said. 